# Audience

## Primary persona
- Role: SEO practitioner, agency owner, or in-house SEO/content lead at a SaaS or DTC brand
- Skill level: knows what GSC, schema, and core web vitals are. Has used Ahrefs or SEMrush. Has shipped content before. Do not over-explain SEO basics.
- The problem: their existing playbook from 2022-2024 is degrading. AI Overviews are eating clicks. Old posts are decaying faster than they can refresh them. They want concrete tactics for 2026, not "AI is changing everything" hot takes.
- Already tried: generic SEO advice, agency retainers, hiring writers, AI tools that produce mush. Burned by both extremes.
- Willing to pay for: tools and tactics that demonstrably move rankings or save them serious time.

## What this audience hates
- "What is SEO" intro paragraphs
- Listicles without an opinion ("17 ways to rank!")
- Vague advice ("create high quality content")
- "Game-changing" / "revolutionary" framing
- AI-generated content that smells like AI
- Affiliate spam disguised as guides
- Over-explaining basics
- Posts that take 800 words to make a 3-sentence point
- Conclusions that summarise the post you just read
